---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="UX Review Agent">

  <section class="agent-intro">
    <p class="agent-eyebrow">Agent Guide</p>
    <h1 class="agent-h1">UX Review</h1>
    <p class="agent-summary">
      The UX Review agent audits any live Myprotein page for UX, accessibility, and conversion
      issues. Give it a myprotein.com URL and it captures screenshots via a dedicated script,
      inspects the DOM and computed styles against the Myprotein design system, and produces a
      structured report — every finding rated by severity, with a specific recommendation and
      a screenshot showing the exact problem. Use it before a redesign, after a release, or as
      ongoing design debt tracking.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Before you start ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Before you start</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>The full URL of the Myprotein page you want reviewed (e.g. <code>https://www.myprotein.com/sports-nutrition/impact-whey-protein/10530943.html</code>)</li>
      <li>The page must be publicly accessible — the agent cannot handle pages that require login</li>
      <li>You're running Claude Code inside this repo — the screenshot script and report file both write to the local filesystem</li>
      <li>Node.js is available on your machine (the screenshot script runs via <code>node scripts/screenshot.mjs</code>)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── How to trigger ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How to trigger it</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">Use the slash command directly, or describe what you want in plain English — the agent recognises all of these:</p>
    <div class="trigger-block">
      <code class="trigger-command">/myprotein-ux-review</code>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-examples">
      <span class="trigger-chip">"review this Myprotein page [URL]"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"audit the basket UX"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"check the product page UX on this URL"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"how's the UX on the checkout?"</span>
    </div>
    <p class="guide-body guide-body--tip">Include the URL in the same message as the trigger. If you don't, the agent will ask for it before starting.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step-by-step walkthrough ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Step-by-step walkthrough</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">1</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Screenshots via the screenshot script</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent runs the dedicated screenshot script — not the browser tool — which correctly
            dismisses cookie banners, newsletter modals, and other overlays before capturing.
            It auto-selects the right config based on the URL: PDP pages get above-fold, product
            panel, accordion, FBT, reviews, and ATB crop; PLP pages get above-fold, filters, and
            product grid; all other pages get above-fold, mid, and lower.
            Screenshots are saved directly to <code>src/assets/reports/[report-slug]/</code>.
          </p>
          <pre class="code-block">node scripts/screenshot.mjs "&lt;url&gt;" "&lt;report-slug&gt;"</pre>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">2</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Page type is identified</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent checks <code>references/page-types.md</code> to understand what the page is
            supposed to achieve and what the critical conversion path is. A PDP audit focuses
            differently from a basket audit — this step ensures the right sections get the right
            scrutiny.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">3</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Desktop and mobile audit</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Working through the page top to bottom using the screenshots as visual reference,
            the agent uses the browser tool for DOM inspection only — not for additional screenshots.
            It assesses above-the-fold clarity, CTA prominence, navigation, product/content
            presentation, friction points, and form usability. Mobile is assessed by inspecting
            responsive classes and hidden/shown elements — tap target sizes, CTA accessibility
            without excessive scrolling, and text legibility.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">4</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Design consistency check</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent loads <code>references/design-tokens.md</code> — the exact hex codes,
            spacing values, border radii, and type specs from the Myprotein design system — and
            uses DevTools to compare computed styles against them. It checks: colours on CTAs,
            headings, badges, and banners; spacing on cards and buttons (valid values: 4, 8, 12,
            16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64px); border radii (cards: 12px, CTA: 32px, chips: 8px);
            and the Figtree font family. Any hardcoded overrides or deviations are flagged.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">5</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Findings are rated and written up</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Each issue is rated High, Medium, or Low based on conversion impact — a contrast
            failure on the Add to Basket button is High; the same issue in the footer is Low.
            The agent writes a structured finding for each: what the problem is, the conversion
            or usability impact, and a specific recommended fix. Low-confidence observations
            without screenshot or DOM evidence are discarded.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">6</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Report file is written and index updated</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent writes <code>src/pages/reports/[slug].astro</code> using the
            <code>ReportLayout</code> and <code>FindingCard</code> components, with screenshots
            referenced directly from assets. It also adds an entry to
            <code>src/pages/reports/index.astro</code> so the report appears in the dashboard.
            Both files are ready to commit with no manual edits needed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Committing the output ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Committing the output</h2>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Files created</h3>
    <ul class="file-list">
      <li><code>src/pages/reports/[slug].astro</code> — the report page</li>
      <li><code>src/assets/reports/[slug]/*.png</code> — screenshots (typically 4–10 files)</li>
      <li><code>src/pages/reports/index.astro</code> — updated with the new report entry</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Git commands</h3>
    <pre class="code-block">git add src/pages/reports/[slug].astro src/assets/reports/[slug]/
git add src/pages/reports/index.astro
git commit -m "Add UX review: [Page Name] ([date])"
git push</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Suggested commit message format</h3>
    <pre class="code-block">Add UX review: Impact Whey PDP (2026-06-01)</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Verifying the report is live</h3>
    <p class="guide-body">
      After pushing, Vercel will redeploy automatically (usually under 2 minutes). Visit
      <code>/reports/[slug]</code> on the deployed site to confirm the page is live, screenshots
      load, and finding cards render correctly. You can also check the dashboard at
      <code>/reports</code> to confirm the new entry appears.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Tips and common issues ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Tips and common issues</h2>
    <ul class="tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Screenshot shows a half-loaded state.</strong>
        Lazy-loaded images or components sometimes don't render in the screenshot script. If a
        screenshot looks broken or empty, ask the agent to re-run with an explicit wait instruction
        — <em>"wait for the product grid to load before screenshotting"</em>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Page requires login (account pages, checkout).</strong>
        The agent cannot authenticate. For these pages, provide a screenshot directly and describe
        the elements you want assessed — the agent can still write a structured finding card
        from your description without navigating the page itself.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cookie consent banner blocks the view.</strong>
        The screenshot script attempts to dismiss banners automatically. If it can't, the agent
        notes it in the report and captures what it can. You can re-run after manually clearing
        cookies or with a direct link that bypasses the banner.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Fewer findings than expected.</strong>
        Zero or very few findings is a valid result — it means the page is in good shape against
        the design system and conversion checklist. Don't prompt the agent to find more issues;
        that produces inflated, low-confidence findings that aren't useful.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Report page has broken image paths after committing.</strong>
        Check that the PNG filenames in the <code>.astro</code> file exactly match the files in
        <code>src/assets/reports/[slug]/</code>. Astro image imports are case-sensitive.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .agent-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .agent-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .agent-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .agent-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .guide-section { margin-bottom: 52px; }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .sub-heading {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin: 20px 0 8px;
  }

  .guide-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-body--tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .checklist li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .checklist li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .trigger-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .trigger-command {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    padding: 8px 18px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .trigger-examples {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .trigger-chip {
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-chip);
    padding: 5px 12px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .code-block {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    border: var(--card-border);
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .file-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .file-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 16px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .file-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .steps { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 34px;
    height: 34px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .step-title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .step-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .tips-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .tips-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
  }
  .tips-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
</style>
